snippet.title: The 10 Year Old Murder of Amber Tucarro | Hitchhiker Kidnapped & Killed | Her Last Phone Call Alive
snippet.description:
Between 7:30pm and 8:30pm on August 18th, 2010, Amber Tucarro left the Nisku Place Motel, located near the Edmonton international Airport, with plans to travel to Edmonton. Some state she went out to buy food and others say she was excited to see Edmonton for the first time. That evening, Amber had been hitchhiking before entering the vehicle of an unknown male. This is the last known sighting of Amber Tucarro. Her remains were discovered two years after her disappearance. The only concrete evidence affiliated with the case is a one minute clip of a telephone conversation Amber had the night she went missing. In the call, Amber can be heard arguing with an anonymous man allegedly driving her into town. The man in the tape has never been identified and the case remains unsolved. If you prefer more graphic or gruesome content, check out some of my 18+ videos down below.
